reviews.text: Oldest existing publing estate in tuen mun with very convinient transportaton facilities,bus terminus 7-8 bus stops arround this estate 3 light rail stops ,mcdonald's,superarkets,shopping mall, about 10 mints walking distance from both siu hong and tuen mun west rail
A large public estate with decades of history. You don't have to go there if you're not live there.

The oldest public estate in Tuen Mun, the wall of buildings like a slide and the shopping center is small and no air-con, many old and traditional shops here, e.g. stationaries shop, grocery shop etc, they are still selling some 70-80’s products and some of them are made in Hong Kong, like the “Red A” plastic products. You can also find some interesting stationaries here. There also has a small library, many people stay here for whole day, although there is small, kid corner occupy 30% area of the library, care about kids very much.
They have to fix it up and lower the cost more.
